      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions must be measured and documented with uncertainty bounds matching simulation inlet/outlet specifications.",
      "rationale": "Experiments were performed under controlled laboratory conditions; inlet flow rates were measured with Coriolis meters (±1%). Rotational speed uncertainty was ±10 RPM. Temperature was not controlled to match CFD assumptions. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) must be computed with combined experimental and simulation uncertainty for each QOI.",
      "rationale": "Percent error between predicted and measured hemolysis index was computed at all five operating points. Combined uncertainty interval was estimated via Monte Carlo. Formal validation metric per ASME V&V 20 was not computed. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QOIs must directly correspond to the clinical decision QOI (absolute hemolysis index) with no surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "Validation employed the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) as the primary QOI, which is the same metric used in the clinical decision threshold. Transformation from raw plasma hemoglobin to NIH introduces an additional uncertainty source not fully propagated. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump geometry was used in both validation experiments and COU simulations. Porcine blood was used in experiments; human blood rheology was assumed in COU simulations. Operating speed range partially overlaps COU envelope. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
